      "id": "classical_mechanics-newtonian-dynamics",
      "name": "Newtonian Dynamics",
      "description": "Newtonian dynamics solves motion from forces: free-body diagrams identify every force on each body, a coordinate system is chosen, and Newton's second law F = ma is written per body; constraint forces are added as needed, giving equations of motion that integrate to the trajectory x(t) and velocity v(t).",
