      "id": "classical_mechanics-hamiltonian-mechanics",
      "name": "Hamiltonian Mechanics",
      "description": "Hamiltonian mechanics recasts dynamics in phase space: conjugate momenta are defined from the Lagrangian and a Legendre transform builds the Hamiltonian H(q,p,t); when time does not appear explicitly H is the conserved energy, and Hamilton's canonical equations give first-order flow of position and momentum.",
